$ PowerShell: preference variables

Preference variables are created by → Windows/PowerShell and assigned default values. The user of a → → Windows/PowerShell/session[session] can change them according to his/her preferences.

`$ConfirmPreference`

`$DebugPreference`

`$ErrorActionPreference`

`$ErrorView`

`$FormatEnumerationLimit`

→ Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/preference/MaximumAliasCount[`$MaximumAliasCount`]

→ Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/preference/MaximumDriveCount[`$MaximumDriveCount`]

`$MaximumErrorCount`

→ Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/preference/MaximumFunctionCount[`$MaximumFunctionCount`]

`$MaximumHistoryCount`

→ Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/preference/MaximumVariableCount[`$MaximumVariableCount`]

→ Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/preference/OFS[`$OFS`]

→ Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/preference/OutputEncoding[`$OutputEncoding`]

`$ProgressReference`

`$VerbosePreference`

`$WarningPreference`

`$WhatIfPreference`

